      <title>Gay Block began photographing her mother, Bertha Alyce, in 1973 and continued un...</title>
      <link>https://www.instagram.com/p/DDAlLB_yPvq/</link>
      <description><![CDATA[<p><img src="https://scontent-cph2-1.cdninstagram.com/v/t51.75761-15/468989352_18366263656118264_4793544695959254626_n.jpg?stp=dst-jpg_e35_tt6&amp;_nc_cat=102&amp;ig_cache_key=MzUxMjk3MTE5NTEyODAxOTk0Ng%3D%3D.3-ccb7-5&amp;ccb=7-5&amp;_nc_sid=58cdad&amp;efg=eyJ2ZW5jb2RlX3RhZyI6InhwaWRzLjEwODB4OTQ2LnNkci5DMyJ9&amp;_nc_ohc=Wf6TBuPQMY0Q7kNvwGPEHfL&amp;_nc_oc=AdqWo-WkLPy6gVL1mBrDeojYTI8Q5Lp6j4KbzsfiZfKVbkigr-zHxQfAbPkkzNgoOto&amp;_nc_ad=z-m&amp;_nc_cid=0&amp;_nc_zt=23&amp;se=7&amp;_nc_ht=scontent-cph2-1.cdninstagram.com&amp;_nc_gid=1fbf5d67pfYDe1PLXb5YHQ&amp;_nc_ss=7a338&amp;oh=00_AfyZURs7GyK9DaMJNNrP5antsuT_9Iaqaf_BO2Ppp6mlmA&amp;oe=69C8D3BE" alt="Instagram billede fra @3rdritual" /></p><p><strong>@3rdritual</strong></p><p>Gay Block began photographing her mother, Bertha Alyce, in 1973 and continued until she passed in 1991. “But it was after she died,” Block shared in an interview about the work, “that I learned the most about her. <br/>
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀<br/>
“I began to understand that her anger had its origins in all she had not been able to do because she was a woman.”<br/>
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀<br/>
Image: Mothers jewelry boxes, “Bertha Alyce: Mother Exposed” by Gay Block, 2003</p>]]></description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><img src="https://scontent-cph2-1.cdninstagram.com/v/t51.75761-15/468989352_18366263656118264_4793544695959254626_n.jpg?stp=dst-jpg_e35_tt6&amp;_nc_cat=102&amp;ig_cache_key=MzUxMjk3MTE5NTEyODAxOTk0Ng%3D%3D.3-ccb7-5&amp;ccb=7-5&amp;_nc_sid=58cdad&amp;efg=eyJ2ZW5jb2RlX3RhZyI6InhwaWRzLjEwODB4OTQ2LnNkci5DMyJ9&amp;_nc_ohc=Wf6TBuPQMY0Q7kNvwGPEHfL&amp;_nc_oc=AdqWo-WkLPy6gVL1mBrDeojYTI8Q5Lp6j4KbzsfiZfKVbkigr-zHxQfAbPkkzNgoOto&amp;_nc_ad=z-m&amp;_nc_cid=0&amp;_nc_zt=23&amp;se=7&amp;_nc_ht=scontent-cph2-1.cdninstagram.com&amp;_nc_gid=1fbf5d67pfYDe1PLXb5YHQ&amp;_nc_ss=7a338&amp;oh=00_AfyZURs7GyK9DaMJNNrP5antsuT_9Iaqaf_BO2Ppp6mlmA&amp;oe=69C8D3BE" alt="Instagram billede fra @3rdritual" /></p><p><strong>@3rdritual</strong></p><p>Gay Block began photographing her mother, Bertha Alyce, in 1973 and continued until she passed in 1991. “But it was after she died,” Block shared in an interview about the work, “that I learned the most about her. <br/>
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀<br/>
“I began to understand that her anger had its origins in all she had not been able to do because she was a woman.”<br/>
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀<br/>
Image: Mothers jewelry boxes, “Bertha Alyce: Mother Exposed” by Gay Block, 2003</p>]]></content:encoded>
